         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">18/3/78. ¶  ¶ I thank you, dear Mr Buchanan, ¶  for sending me the small-leaved Veronica which in many respects is very interesting. Your Dichelachnes I will carefully examine, when I get my extensive...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">78.03.18</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">To John Buchanan</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">A644, Mitchell Library, State Library of New South Wales, Sydney.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">18/3/78.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I thank you, dear Mr Buchanan,<note xml:id="ftn1" type="footnote" n="1">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">John Buchanan (1819-1898).</p>
               </note> for sending me the small-leaved Veronica which in many respects is very interesting. Your Dichelachnes I will carefully examine, when I get my extensive series of specimens of that genus accessible again, they having been lent with all my other <name key="Gramineae">Gramineae</name> for Mr Bentham's use in the elaboration of the 7th vol of the fl. Austral.<note xml:id="ftn2" type="footnote" n="2">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">Bentham (1863-78), vol. 7.</p>
               </note>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>The position of the arista, dorsal or nearly terminal, mainly distinguishes the two species. you quite correctly recognized the true <name key="Dichelachne%20sciurea">Dichelachne sciurea</name>, but my impression is that it cannot be separated from Cavanilles <name key="Stipa%20micrantha">Stipa micrantha</name>, as mentioned in my fragm. VIII, 105.<note xml:id="ftn3" type="footnote" n="3">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">B73.11.03.</p>
               </note> Indeed I regard Dichelachne only as a section of Stipa, though Bentham places it next to <name key="Agrostis">Agrostis</name>. Steudel described several Dichelachnes, the definition of which I will compare with your supposed form of D. crinita, as soon as I can get at my specimens again.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I think, that I mentioned to you before the fact, that I find <name key="Stylidium%20subulatum">Stylidium subulatum</name> to be a true <name key="Forstera">Forstera</name> or <name key="Phyllachne">Phyllachne</name>.<note xml:id="ftn4" type="footnote" n="4">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">No earlier letter to Buchanan with this information has been found, but he had mentioned it to another NZ correspondent, M to F. Hutton, 13 May 1877. See B78.06.01.</p>
               </note>
            </p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">Regardfully your</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Ferd. von Mueller.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">The numbers of stamens in Dichelachne should be carefully observed. Can you kindly procure for me specimens of your two <name key="Zostera">Zostera</name>s with ripe fruits? I imagine, that not all your oceanic <name key="Monocotyledoneae">Monocotyledoneae</name> are as yet fully known.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>There is also a fresh water plant, allied to <name key="Hydropeltis">Hydropeltis</name> &amp; <name key="Cabomba">Cabomba</name>, in your islands, of which I have only one imperfect specimen, which as yet prevents me to identify it with any of the American species. Did you never see it? How far south grows your <name key="Kentia">Kentia</name> Palm</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>N.Z seeds more always useful to me for foreign interchanges.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
